According to this story in the Star: "The number of people in Ontario with diabetes more than doubled in the decade between 1995 and 2005, according to a new study by Toronto researchers."

http://www.thestar.com/News/article/187318

Diabetes is disease whose health impact is often underestimated - in fact it is a gateway to numerous other conditions including kidney and heart problems, blindness and amputation.  Because of this, it is particularly responsible for the current 

New York Times series 'The Stealth Epidemic'
http://topics.nytimes.com/top/news/health/diseasesconditionsandhealthtopics/diabetes/index.html


